---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Writing" description="Long-form essays on design, technology, and craft.">
  <div class="pt-[var(--space-9)]">
    <h1 class="text-display font-display text-[var(--color-fg)]">Writing</h1>
    <p class="mt-4 font-mono text-[var(--text-meta)] tracking-[var(--tracking-meta)] text-[var(--color-muted)]">
      Essays on design, typography, and building for the web.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="mt-12 max-w-reading space-y-8">
    <article class="pb-8 border-b border-[var(--color-border)]">
      <a href="/writing/typography-as-interface" class="group block">
        <h2 class="text-title font-display text-[var(--color-fg)] group-hover:text-[var(--color-accent)] transition-colors duration-[var(--motion-fast)]">Typography as Interface</h2>
        <div class="mt-2 font-mono text-[var(--text-meta)] tracking-[var(--tracking-meta)] text-[var(--color-muted)] flex gap-4">
          <time datetime="2026-04-08">2026-04-08</time>
          <span>8 min read</span>
        </div>
        <p class="mt-3 text-[var(--text-body)] text-[var(--color-fg-muted)]">
          When typography is the primary visual system, every decision about type is a decision about interface. This essay explores what happens when you stop decorating and start reading.
        </p>
      </a>
    </article>

    <article class="pb-8 border-b border-[var(--color-border)]">
      <a href="/writing/against-decoration" class="group block">
        <h2 class="text-title font-display text-[var(--color-fg)] group-hover:text-[var(--color-accent)] transition-colors duration-[var(--motion-fast)]">Against Decoration</h2>
        <div class="mt-2 font-mono text-[var(--text-meta)] tracking-[var(--tracking-meta)] text-[var(--color-muted)] flex gap-4">
          <time datetime="2026-03-29">2026-03-29</time>
          <span>6 min read</span>
        </div>
        <p class="mt-3 text-[var(--text-body)] text-[var(--color-fg-muted)]">
          The modern web is drowning in visual noise. Gradients, glassmorphism, animated backgrounds. What if the antidote is restraint?
        </p>
      </a>
    </article>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
